  "text": "The obtained clusters were inspected in several anatomical ROIs specified by the Automated Anatomical Labeling (AAL) atlas [CITATION_1] . The most concurrent regions activated in response to viewing food pictures were selected according to the meta-analyses [CITATION_2] 29] , i.e. fusiform gyrus, middle and superior occipital gyrus, lingual gyrus, lateral OFC (Frontal Mid Orb), insular cortex and amygdala. The parietal gyrus was not investigated because this region was outside the covered block in HR condition.",
